Texts.Eng: A big ol' metal bookcase. Nothing I'd want to read, though.
Texts.Chs: 一个大的金属书架。不过，我什么都不想读。

Texts.Eng: A lot of Skath-related books. A few of them are readable, but most are written in the language of the Skath.
Texts.Chs: 很多与绘世者有关的书。其中一些是可读的，但大多数是用绘世者语写的。

Texts.Eng: A secure bookcase for all kinds of books.
Texts.Chs: 存放各种书籍的安全书柜。

Texts.Eng: Floran hasss no time for sssilly waterdragon booksss.
Texts.Chs: 叶族人没有时间去看愚蠢的水龙书店。

Texts.Eng: It seems the Skath have never developed advanced robotics.
Texts.Chs: 似乎绘世者从未开发过先进的机器人技术。

Texts.Eng: Many Skath like to read in their free time, when they are not at work.
Texts.Chs: 很多人喜欢在空闲时间读书，而不是在工作的时候。

Texts.Eng: Reading through the Skath's history, I can begin to understand their xenophobia.
Texts.Chs: 通过阅读绘世者的历史，我可以开始理解他们的仇外心理。

Texts.Eng: The Skath have comic books?! This 'Skathman' looks eerily similar to a superhero in human comics...
Texts.Chs: 绘世者有漫画书吗？！这个“绘世者侠”看起来很像人类漫画中的超级英雄。。。

Texts.Eng: There are a lot of books. It looks like the Skath don't devote much writing to their myths.
Texts.Chs: 有很多书。看来绘世者并没有为他们的神话写太多东西。
